headline: Software Stocks Are Having Another Ugly Day
summary: The weeks-long selloff in software stocks deepened Monday amid general unease about the threat posed by AI. Software-makers AppLovin, CrowdStrike, Datadog, Workday, Expedia and Intuit were all among the S&P 500's worst 10 performers around midday, dropping at least 7%.

headline: Workday Brings Back Founder CEO As AI Focus Reshapes Investor Expectations
summary: Workday co-founder Aneel Bhusri is returning as CEO, replacing Carl Eschenbach. The leadership transition centers on accelerating Workday's AI strategy in its core enterprise software offerings. Investors are watching how this shift affects Workday's positioning against AI focused competitors. Workday, trading on NasdaqGS:WDAY, is making this leadership change at a time when its share price stands at $137.81.
